cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.SI, cs.CL. 

The paper deals with author name disambiguation in bibliometric databases, which is a topic that is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as it directly deals with bibliometric data. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DB (Databases) are also likely categories as they deal with data management and retrieval. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are less likely but still possible categories as they deal with network analysis and natural language processing, which could be relevant to the disambiguation task.
